6 Conclusion
We have shown that curved uid membranes behave laterally as an effective viscoelastic medium, even if the membrane uidity is purely viscous. Consequently, the lateral mobility of a membrane inclusion is frequency-dependent, and the effective storage modulus is non-zero. At the root of this result is the observation that the lateral motion of a probe generates a non-uniform interfacial ow, which in the presence of curvature creates a shape deformation mobilizing the out-of-plane viscoelastic response. To capture this effect, two theoretical ingredients developed here are essential: (1) a general formulation of the interfacial hydrodynamics at nite curvature, and (2) the linearization of the governing equations around a curved state.
